		{
			dependencies: [
				"6389E73010F05D4B"
				"69561C5FE389E808"
				"5D74D6F0E45BC71C"
			]
			description: ["The &lAssembler&r can automate some crafting recipes, if you want a way more expensive version of a mechanical crafter, for some reason. But where it truly shines is with its exclusive recipes, like the recipe to make blast furnace coils. &eIt can also make circuit components much more efficiently!!!"]
			id: "5E03AFFA39D5E340"
			subtitle: "ASSembler"
			tasks: [{
				id: "52A6DF550C728947"
				item: "gtceu:lv_assembler"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 3.5d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1790658601A1E187"]
			description: [
				"&lConductive Mixed-Salts Alloy&r, or &oCMSA&r, is the first &7LV&r superconductor. This means that wires made of this material will have &ono energy loss at all&r, so feel free to make power lines as long as you want!"
				""
				"By the end of LV/LMV, you will have &eManganese phosphide&r wires, which are also &7LV&r superconductors but they have a higher amperage than CMSA wires. This means that they can transmit more energy, so they're an upgrade."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&d\"GRRRRRR THIS ISNT REALISTIC ITS NOT IN REAL LIFE I HAVE NEVER, EVER ENCOUNTERED THIS AT MY 67 YEARS OF WORKING AT CERN!!!!!! I HATE THIS PACK!!!!!\"&r -The crustiest, greasiest greghead"
			]
			icon: "gtceu:conductive_mixed_salts_alloy_ingot"
			id: "0493F54BBA7B53CA"
			shape: "pentagon"
			subtitle: "Your First Superconductor"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "722122A28140EC1F"
					item: "gtceu:conductive_mixed_salts_alloy_ingot"
					type: "item"
